    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bowl Is Important to Rutgers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Barbara Res letter contends that participation in Texas Bowl is important to Rutgers University football team (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>As a 50-something returning student, I got a kick out of attending Rutgers University with the excitement its football team brought to even our remote Newark campus. But your article stressed the relative unimportance of the Texas Bowl and implied that winning this trophy would have been an embarrassment to a real team (''Red-Letter Day for Scarlet Knights,'' Dec. 29). An article can be beautifully written without being sardonic.</p>
        <p>Barbara Res  Old Tappan, N.J.</p>
      </block>
